{"id":14881121,"mediaExerciseId":"690cce6d-39a0-4cfc-b806-23b05e9dc54f","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"8","chapterTitle":"Stock Valuation","groupId":612321,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":265,"solutions":[{"id":6048097,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we have to find out the **required return**. The formula we will use for the calculation is the dividend growth model.\n\n$$\n\\begin{align}\nP_0&= \\frac{D_1}{R-g}\n\\end{align}\n$$\n\nWhere,\n\n$$\n\\begin{align}\nR&= \\frac{D_1}{P_0}+g\n\\end{align}\n$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"We have the following information.\n\n* The dividend payment $D_1$ is equal to $\\$2.34$\n\n* The current sell $P_0$ is equal to $\\$37$\n\n* The growth rate $g$ is equal to $4.5\\%.$\n\nNow, let's do the calculation according to the formula which we denote with $(2).$\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nR&=\\frac{D_1}{P_0} + g\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{\\$2.34}{\\$37}+4.5\\%\\\\[12pt]\n&=\\frac{\\$2.34}{\\$37}+0.045\\\\[12pt]\n&=0.06324+ 0.045\\\\[7pt]\n&=0.1082\\\\[7pt]\n&=10.82\\%.\n\\end{align*}$$\n\n\nTherefore, we can conclude that the required return is $\\boxed{10.82\\%.}$\n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"$\\boxed{10.82\\%.}$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"aeaba02e-57e2-4bc4-8506-7e78d2474579","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0